1 AMEND House Committee Substitute for House Bill No. 1871, Page 1, Section A, Line 4, by
2 inserting after said section and line the following:
3
4 "9.515. August twelfth each year is hereby designated as "Election Worker Appreciation
5 Day" in Missouri. The citizens of this state are encouraged to participate in appropriate events
6 and activities to celebrate the essential contributions of election workers and express
7 appreciation for the vital role they play in elections.
8 108.240. 1. Before any general obligation bearer bond or general obligation registered
9 bond, hereafter issued by any county, township, city, town, village or school district or special
10 road district or fire protection district or by virtue of the provisions of chapters 243, 245, 248,
11 and sections 242.010 to 242.690 for any purpose whatever, shall obtain validity or be negotiated:
12 (1) If such bonds are in bearer form, such bonds shall first be presented to the state
13 auditor, who, other provisions of law notwithstanding, shall certify by manual or facsimile
14 endorsement of such bonds that all conditions of the laws have been complied with in its issue, if
15 that be the case, and also that the conditions of the contract, under which they were ordered to be
16 issued, have also been complied with and the evidence of that fact shall be filed and preserved by
17 the auditor. The state auditor may endorse bearer bonds with the auditor's facsimile signature in
18 lieu of manual signature after filing the auditor's manual signature, certified by the auditor under
19 oath, with the secretary of state; and
20 (2) If such bonds are in registered form, the proceedings relating to the issuance of such
21 registered bonds shall first be presented to the state auditor, who shall examine the same and
22 shall issue a certificate that such proceedings comply with all conditions of the laws, if that be
23 the case, and also that the conditions of the contract, under which they were ordered to be issued,
24 have also been complied with, and the evidence of these facts shall be filed and preserved by the
25 auditor. The state auditor shall also maintain the following information: the name of the issuer
26 of the bonds; the amount thereof; the maturity dates thereof; the interest rates thereon; and the
27 provisions with respect to prepayment, if any.
28 2. Such bearer bonds after receiving the said certificate of the auditor as herein provided
29 and such registered bonds after the issuance of the said certificate as herein provided shall
30 thereafter be held in every action, suit or proceeding in which their validity is, or may be,
