1 brought into question, prima facie, valid and binding obligations, and in every action brought to
2 enforce collection of such bonds, the certificate of such auditor, or a duly certified copy thereof,
3 shall be admitted and received in evidence of the validity of such bonds, together with the
4 coupons thereto attached if any; provided, the only defense which can be offered against the
5 validity of such bonds shall be for forgery or fraud. But this section shall not be construed to
6 give validity to any such bonds as may be issued in excess of the limit fixed by the constitution,
7 or contrary to its provisions, but all such bonds shall, to the extent of such excess, be held void;
8 and provided further, that the remedy of injunction shall also lie at the instance of any taxpayer
9 of the respective county, city, town, village, township or school district or special road district or
10 fire protection district or drainage district or levy district to prevent the registration of any bonds,
11 alleged to be illegally issued or funded.
12 3. For purposes of subsection 1 of this section, once the time period set forth in section
13 115.557 has expired, if no election contest has been brought, all conditions of chapter 115 shall
14 be deemed as having been complied with in the issuance of the bond."; and
15
16 Further amend said bill, Pages 2-3, Section 115.127, Lines 16-29, by deleting said lines and
17 inserting in lieu thereof the following:
18
19 "2. Except as provided in subsections 1 and 4 of this section and in sections 115.521,
20 115.549 and 115.593, the election authority shall cause legal notice of each election held in its
21 jurisdiction to be published. The notice shall be published in two newspapers of different
22 political faith and qualified pursuant to chapter 493 which are published within the bounds of the
23 area holding the election. If there is only one so-qualified newspaper, then notice shall be
24 published in only one newspaper. If there is no newspaper published within the bounds of the
25 election area, then the notice shall be published in two qualified newspapers of different political
26 faith serving the area. Notice shall be published twice[, the first publication occurring in the
27 second week prior to the election, and the second publication occurring] within [one week] six
28 weeks prior to the election. Each such legal notice shall include the date and time of the
29 election, the name of the officer or agency calling the election and a sample ballot; and, unless
30 notice has been given as provided by section 115.129, the second publication of notice of the
31 election shall include the location of polling places. The election authority may provide any
32 additional notice of the election it deems desirable."; and
33
34 Further amend said bill and section, Page 3, Lines 35-41, by deleting said lines and inserting in
35 lieu thereof the following:
36
37 "4. In lieu of causing legal notice to be published twice in accordance with any of the
38 provisions of this chapter, the election authority [in jurisdictions which have less than seven
39 hundred fifty registered voters and in which no newspaper qualified pursuant to chapter 493 is
Page 2 of 3

5033H04.05H
1 published,] may cause legal notice to be mailed [during the second week prior to the election, by
2 first class mail,] within six weeks prior to the election to each registered voter at the voter's
3 voting address and published once in one or more newspapers in the county. An election
4 authority may exclude from this mailing any voter that is designated as an inactive voter
5 pursuant to section 115.193. All such legal notices shall include the date and time of the
6 election, the location of the polling place, the name of the officer or agency calling the election
7 and a sample ballot."; and
8
9 Further amend said bill by amending the title, enacting clause, and intersectional references
10 accordingly.
